<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Ride Confirmation</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f4f4f4 0%, #ffcc00 100%);
            background-size: 200% 200%;
            animation: gradientBackground 5s ease 1;
        }



        .container {
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            max-width: 600px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
        }

        p {
            color: #666;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .footer {
            margin-top: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #999;
        }

        .confirmed-text {
            font-size: 50px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            animation: pulse 1.5s infinite alternate;
        }


    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <div class="confirmed-text">Confirmed</div>
    <h1>Ride Confirmation</h1>
    <p>Dear @Model.RiderName,</p>
    <p>Your ride has been confirmed. Please review the details below:</p>
    <p><strong>Driver email:</strong> @Model.DriverEmail</p>
    <p><strong>Driver phone:</strong> @Model.DriverPhone</p>
    <p><strong>Driver name:</strong> @Model.DriverName</p>
    <p><strong>Start at:</strong> @Model.PickupLocation</p>
    <p><strong>End at:</strong> @Model.DestinationLocation</p>
    <p><strong>Price is:</strong> @Model.Price</p>

    <a href="https://hagglehaul.azurewebsites.net" target="_blank">Click here to manage your trips</a>

    <div class="footer">
        <p>This is an automated email, please do not reply.</p>
        <p><strong>This email is send to :</strong> @Model.RiderEmail</p>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
